headline: Why Airline Stocks Are Flying High Today
summary: Shares of JetBlue Airways (NASDAQ: JBLU) traded up 10% as of 10 a.m. ET, and shares of United Airlines Holdings (NASDAQ: UAL), Delta Air Lines (NYSE: DAL), American Airlines Group (NASDAQ: AAL), and Southwest Airlines (NYSE: LUV) were all up more than 5%.  Historically, airlines have been a bad sector to invest in during a recession.

headline: DAL Q1 Earnings: Revenue Beats Expectations, Profit Misses Amid Capacity and Cost Controls
summary: Global airline Delta Air Lines (NYSE:DAL) reported Q1 CY2025 results topping the market’s revenue expectations, with sales up 2.1% year on year to $14.04 billion. Guidance for next quarter’s revenue was optimistic at $16.66 billion at the midpoint, 2.3% above analysts’ estimates. Its GAAP profit of $0.37 per share was 6.9% below analysts’ consensus estimates.
